WEBVTT

00:07.641 --> 00:10.010
Nice muffler!

00:10.043 --> 00:11.712
We should definitely be
getting a ride.

00:11.745 --> 00:13.446
Right here is
the best spot.

00:13.479 --> 00:14.480
This is cool.

00:15.381 --> 00:16.382
Hitchhiking.

00:16.416 --> 00:19.019
It's, like,
in Kerouac, you know?

00:19.052 --> 00:20.654
Kerouac?

00:21.421 --> 00:22.689
Jack Kerouac.

00:22.723 --> 00:24.390
He wrote
<i>On the Road.</i>

00:24.424 --> 00:27.093
Kim, we've been reading
it in English class

00:27.127 --> 00:29.362
for the last two weeks.
Where've you been?

00:29.395 --> 00:31.164
All we ever do
in that class is read.

00:31.197 --> 00:34.067
Ooh! Stick out
your thumb, would ya?

00:34.100 --> 00:35.969
We're so sheltered,
you know?

00:36.002 --> 00:38.672
There's this whole
other America out there.

00:38.705 --> 00:41.107
And the person
who picks us up
could be an artist

00:41.141 --> 00:44.645
or a psychic
or an escaped felon.

00:44.678 --> 00:45.846
It's so exciting.

00:45.879 --> 00:47.047
Okay, one thing
that helps...

00:47.080 --> 00:49.415
Point your boobs
towards the road.

00:53.419 --> 00:54.588
Redneck!

00:56.222 --> 00:57.691
Oops... I mean...

00:57.724 --> 00:59.225
Cool guy.
Come on!

01:05.165 --> 01:07.200
Hey. Drop us as close
to the corner

01:07.233 --> 01:09.536
of Wilson and Elm
as you can.

01:13.574 --> 01:15.041
Hi, I'm Lindsay.

01:15.075 --> 01:16.276
This is Kim.

01:18.011 --> 01:20.781
So, are you from
around these parts?

01:20.814 --> 01:22.683
1210 Lilac Terrace.

01:23.717 --> 01:25.118
Oh.

01:25.719 --> 01:26.787
So what do you do?

01:31.357 --> 01:33.493
You pick up
hitchhikers a lot?

01:41.167 --> 01:42.869
Listen, I know you.

01:42.903 --> 01:44.437
I buy gear from
your dad's store.

01:44.470 --> 01:46.206
I don't think you girls
should be doin' this,

01:46.239 --> 01:48.642
and I feel obliged
to tell him what you're up to.

01:57.250 --> 02:00.220
<i>♪♪ I don't give a damn</i>
<i>'bout my reputation</i>

02:02.222 --> 02:04.858
<i>♪♪ Livin' in the past,</i>
<i>it's a new generation</i>

02:06.960 --> 02:08.895
<i>♪♪ Go and do</i>
<i>what you want to do</i>

02:08.929 --> 02:11.264
<i>♪♪ And that's what</i>
<i>I'm gonna do</i>

02:11.297 --> 02:13.800
<i>♪♪ And I don't give a damn</i>
<i>'bout my bad reputation</i>

02:16.202 --> 02:18.505
<i>♪♪ Oh, no, no, no,</i>
<i>no, no, no, no</i>

02:18.539 --> 02:20.774
<i>♪♪ Not me</i>

02:20.807 --> 02:21.642
<i>♪♪ Whah! No!</i>

02:21.675 --> 02:22.909
<i>♪♪ No, no, no, no,</i>
<i>no, no, no</i>

02:22.943 --> 02:24.110
<i>♪♪ Not me</i>

02:24.144 --> 02:25.712
<i>♪♪ Me, me, me, me</i>

02:25.746 --> 02:28.348
<i>♪♪ I don't give a damn</i>
<i>'bout my reputation</i>

02:30.517 --> 02:33.153
<i>♪♪ I've never been afraid</i>
<i>of any deviation</i>

02:34.755 --> 02:37.190
<i>♪♪ And I don't really care</i>
<i>if you think I'm strange</i>

02:37.223 --> 02:38.992
<i>♪♪ I ain't gonna change</i>

02:39.025 --> 02:42.529
<i>♪♪ And I'm never gonna care</i>
<i>'bout my bad reputation</i>

02:43.664 --> 02:44.765
<i>♪♪ Not me! ♪♪</i>

02:47.868 --> 02:50.403
This... The thumb?

02:50.436 --> 02:52.138
Do you think I don't
know what that means?

02:52.172 --> 02:53.874
I know, Lindsay.

02:53.907 --> 02:56.042
It means,
"Hey, stranger,

02:56.076 --> 02:57.778
"please lock me in your car,

02:57.811 --> 03:00.346
"drive me to God knows where
and murder me."

03:00.380 --> 03:01.915
Dad, you're
overreacting.

03:01.948 --> 03:04.851
Lindsay, I will not
have my daughter
hopping into cars

03:04.885 --> 03:06.319
like some
woman of the night.

03:06.352 --> 03:09.322
You could have been
picked up by Ted Bundy.

03:09.355 --> 03:11.992
Dad, Kim does it
all the time.

03:12.025 --> 03:13.493
Don't be so
overdramatic.

03:13.527 --> 03:16.196
What, her parents
let her hitchhike?

03:17.698 --> 03:18.965
Oh, I don't know.

03:18.999 --> 03:21.001
I bet she doesn't
even have parents.

03:21.034 --> 03:23.103
Of course she does,
Dad.

03:23.136 --> 03:25.238
Mom, you talked
to her mom on the phone.

03:25.271 --> 03:26.740
Well, maybe we should
meet her.

03:26.773 --> 03:29.409
I used to know all
your friends' parents.

03:29.843 --> 03:31.111
You know...

03:31.144 --> 03:32.713
We should invite her
over for dinner.

03:32.746 --> 03:34.047
Get acquainted.

03:34.080 --> 03:35.616
HAROLD: Yeah.

03:35.649 --> 03:37.383
Mom, no. Please?

03:37.417 --> 03:38.819
Yeah, well, I think
she oughta know

03:38.852 --> 03:41.622
what a bad influence her
daughter is, don't you?

03:44.858 --> 03:47.293
All right, guys,
let's play
a little softball.

03:47.327 --> 03:49.262
Pick your team, gents.

03:49.295 --> 03:51.064
Oh, man, here we go.

03:51.097 --> 03:52.132
I've got Lewis.

03:52.165 --> 03:53.734
Got Humphries.

03:56.036 --> 03:57.203
Uh, Heathcliff.

03:57.237 --> 03:58.672
Shawn!
Pick me.

03:59.372 --> 04:00.674
Give me Richie.

04:00.707 --> 04:02.408
Um, Jeremy.

04:02.442 --> 04:04.611
Pick me, pick me.
Give me Nathan.

04:05.912 --> 04:07.247
Winnington.

04:07.714 --> 04:09.583
No... He sucks.

04:09.883 --> 04:10.951
Mike.

04:10.984 --> 04:12.519
I'm good.
Justin.

04:13.587 --> 04:14.621
Henry.

04:15.722 --> 04:17.223
Okay, White.

04:17.257 --> 04:18.692
Yeah!

04:28.001 --> 04:29.335
All right, divvy
'em up. Let's go.

04:29.369 --> 04:30.571
Come on.
Let's go.

04:36.176 --> 04:40.213
<i>♪♪ There is no language</i>
<i>in our lives</i>

04:40.246 --> 04:45.018
<i>♪♪ To tell the world</i>
<i>just how we feel</i>

04:47.487 --> 04:49.523
<i>♪♪ No, no, no, no,</i>
<i>no, no, no, no</i>

04:49.556 --> 04:52.826
<i>♪♪ Bridge of thoughts</i>

04:52.859 --> 04:55.629
<i>♪♪ No mental link</i>

04:55.662 --> 04:59.900
<i>♪♪ No letting out</i>
<i>to start to think</i>

05:04.838 --> 05:08.742
<i>♪♪ There is no language</i>
<i>in our lives</i>

05:08.775 --> 05:12.078
<i>♪♪ Lives, lives</i>

05:12.112 --> 05:16.717
<i>♪♪ Lives</i>

05:17.951 --> 05:21.822
♪♪ <i>There is no muscle</i>
<i>in our tongues</i>

05:21.855 --> 05:25.291
<i>♪♪ Tongues, tongues</i>

05:25.325 --> 05:27.694
<i>♪♪ Tongues ♪♪</i>

05:38.805 --> 05:39.940
Hey.

05:46.312 --> 05:47.781
Hey, Nick.

05:48.849 --> 05:49.883
How's it goin'?

05:49.916 --> 05:51.685
(BELL RINGS)

05:51.718 --> 05:52.853
It's goin'.

05:53.987 --> 05:55.255
Great.

05:55.288 --> 05:57.323
Yeah. It is great.

05:57.357 --> 05:58.825
It's never
been greater.

05:58.859 --> 05:59.926
Hey.

05:59.960 --> 06:01.194
Hey, Kim.

06:01.227 --> 06:04.164
So, what happened
with your parents?
You, like, grounded?

06:04.197 --> 06:06.533
Oh, not exactly.

06:07.333 --> 06:08.935
My parents wanna
meet your mom.

06:10.336 --> 06:11.538
What?

06:11.572 --> 06:13.473
Yeah, they wanna
get to know her.

06:13.840 --> 06:14.875
Shut up.

06:14.908 --> 06:16.777
No, I'm serious.

06:16.810 --> 06:19.079
They're inviting her
over for dinner.

06:19.112 --> 06:20.380
Could you be
quiet, please?

06:20.413 --> 06:21.515
Class is starting.

06:21.548 --> 06:25.519
Today, we are not
in a classroom.

06:26.452 --> 06:30.023
We are in a coffeehouse.

06:30.056 --> 06:33.226
And you are not students.

06:33.259 --> 06:35.562
You are beat poets.

06:36.597 --> 06:39.065
And we're gonna
be reading aloud.

06:39.099 --> 06:41.167
Hey, batta‐batta‐batta.

06:42.202 --> 06:44.070
Swing, batta‐batta‐batta.

06:44.104 --> 06:46.472
Miss! Batta...

06:46.507 --> 06:48.742
Could you be
quiet, please?

06:53.079 --> 06:54.615
Yeah, I'm really
a shortstop.

06:55.315 --> 06:56.750
Is that so?

07:00.921 --> 07:03.289
Hey, they got a meeting
on the mound.

07:03.323 --> 07:04.825
I wonder what
they're talkin' about.

07:05.425 --> 07:06.993
Yeah...

07:07.027 --> 07:08.995
Must be fascinating.

07:09.029 --> 07:10.430
I hate this.

07:10.463 --> 07:11.732
This is so unfair.

07:11.765 --> 07:14.635
Maybe I'm good.
They don't know.

07:14.668 --> 07:17.170
Maybe I'm unbelievably good.

07:17.203 --> 07:18.438
But are they ever
gonna find out?

07:18.471 --> 07:19.973
Uh‐uh. No.

07:20.006 --> 07:21.708
'Cause they never put me
in a position where I can,

07:21.742 --> 07:23.910
where I could catch
a stupid ball.

07:24.344 --> 07:25.746
I hate them.

07:26.647 --> 07:28.782
Maybe they're
scared of you.

07:29.449 --> 07:30.917
Come on, ladies.

07:30.951 --> 07:31.785
Maybe.

07:31.818 --> 07:33.219
(WHISTLING)
Hey, Chuck!

07:33.253 --> 07:34.921
Look alive out there!
Come on!

07:36.723 --> 07:38.024
Let's play some ball.

07:57.210 --> 07:59.479
Oh! Wait.

07:59.513 --> 08:01.214
All the teachers'
numbers are there?

08:02.983 --> 08:04.084
Ooh.

08:04.450 --> 08:05.652
Phone.

08:10.056 --> 08:13.026
Think we could be
arrested for making
prank calls?

08:13.493 --> 08:14.661
Yeah.

08:14.695 --> 08:16.830
And we'll get sent
to telephone prison.

08:17.263 --> 08:18.832
Oh. Ha ha.

08:23.436 --> 08:26.239
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

08:27.073 --> 08:28.709
Hello?

08:28.742 --> 08:31.845
Uh, hmm. Hello?
Coach Fredricks?

08:31.878 --> 08:33.113
<i>Yes.</i>

08:33.146 --> 08:34.648
This is Mr. Crisp.

08:34.681 --> 08:36.850
Gordon Crisp's father.

08:36.883 --> 08:38.018
Mr. Crisp?

08:38.051 --> 08:39.620
Uh, how are you?

08:39.653 --> 08:42.322
<i>Not good. I want to give you</i>
<i>a piece of my mind.</i>

08:42.355 --> 08:43.757
<i>I think</i>
<i>it's very unfair</i>

08:43.790 --> 08:46.593
the way you've been
running baseball in gym class.

08:46.627 --> 08:49.930
<i>You always let</i>
<i>the jock kids run the game.</i>

08:49.963 --> 08:53.333
Now, some kids
like Gordon, my son,

08:53.366 --> 08:54.868
never... Never
get a chance

08:54.901 --> 08:57.003
'cause you guys
think he's not very good.

08:57.037 --> 08:58.972
<i>For example,</i>
<i>he may wanna play shortstop,</i>

08:59.005 --> 09:02.242
<i>but, uh, yeah,</i>
<i>you never give him a shot.</i>

09:02.275 --> 09:06.012
Look, I'm sorry, but, uh,
you know I always assumed

09:06.046 --> 09:08.649
Gordon, uh, didn't
have any interest in sports.

09:08.682 --> 09:10.851
You know what I'm sayin'?
<i>Well, he does.</i>

09:10.884 --> 09:12.686
Don't judge a book
by its cover.

09:12.719 --> 09:14.555
<i>Oh, I... I... I, uh,</i>

09:14.588 --> 09:16.089
I apologize.
All right?

09:16.122 --> 09:17.958
I'll rectify
the situation immediately.

09:17.991 --> 09:20.060
<i>Okay, then.</i>
<i>Thank you very much.</i>

09:20.093 --> 09:21.261
<i>Good‐bye now.</i>

09:21.294 --> 09:22.563
All right, bye.

09:23.997 --> 09:25.799
Gordon Crisp!

09:26.533 --> 09:28.134
I did it.
What did he say?

09:29.102 --> 09:30.537
He totally bought it.

09:30.571 --> 09:32.606
He called me
Mr. Crisp and everything.

09:33.473 --> 09:35.776
Fellas, I just
changed our lives.

09:36.276 --> 09:38.044
Oh, great.

09:38.078 --> 09:40.547
Now we're gonna
have to actually
play baseball.

09:40.581 --> 09:42.616
Thanks a lot, Bill.

09:43.349 --> 09:44.685
I can't wait
till tomorrow.

09:49.690 --> 09:51.558
You have such
a lovely house.

09:51.592 --> 09:52.859
Thank you.

09:53.694 --> 09:55.261
I had a beautiful
house once.

09:55.295 --> 09:56.329
Oh, yeah.

09:56.362 --> 09:57.964
On Maple Drive.

09:57.998 --> 09:59.032
Mm.

09:59.065 --> 10:01.568
Then Kim's father
left me with two kids,

10:01.602 --> 10:04.170
and a huge mortgage
and, well...

10:04.204 --> 10:05.639
That's life, huh?

10:05.672 --> 10:08.374
JEAN: I can't imagine
how difficult it must be

10:08.408 --> 10:09.676
to raise
children by yourself.

10:09.710 --> 10:11.778
Oh, it isn't easy.

10:13.346 --> 10:16.049
Chip, my oldest,
oh, he's a doll.

10:16.082 --> 10:19.252
He's got water in his brain,
but, oh, he's a sweet kid.

10:19.285 --> 10:22.188
Kim, she's
another story.

10:22.222 --> 10:24.390
Yeah, tell us about Kim.

10:24.424 --> 10:27.060
Well, she ain't
the sharpest crayon
in the box.

10:27.093 --> 10:29.329
She's a big
pain in the neck.

10:30.664 --> 10:32.398
And I know she hates me
for being strict...

10:33.499 --> 10:35.035
I get worried.

10:35.068 --> 10:36.202
Of course you do.

10:36.236 --> 10:38.672
Because I don't know
what she's doin' out there.

10:38.705 --> 10:40.507
She lies.

10:40.541 --> 10:42.643
These girls today,
they all lie.

10:43.343 --> 10:44.511
She says to me...

10:44.545 --> 10:45.612
Mm‐hmm.

10:45.646 --> 10:47.614
"I'm gonna go study
at the library."

10:47.648 --> 10:50.651
She goes to a party.
She gets loaded.

10:50.684 --> 10:53.319
She says she's
seein' a movie...

10:53.353 --> 10:56.222
She's foolin' around with
some guy in the back of a van.

10:57.390 --> 10:58.391
Oh, my.

10:59.359 --> 11:00.561
Want to know
how I find out?

11:00.594 --> 11:01.728
How?

11:01.762 --> 11:03.329
I read her diary.

11:04.731 --> 11:07.333
I sneak into her room,
and I read it.

11:07.367 --> 11:09.069
Oh, she won't
do her homework,

11:09.102 --> 11:11.071
but she's got a freakin'
novel in there.

11:11.538 --> 11:13.106
I have to.

11:13.139 --> 11:14.708
It's the only way
I get the truth.

11:14.741 --> 11:16.577
And you wanna
know somethin'?

11:16.610 --> 11:18.512
The truth is very scary.

11:18.545 --> 11:20.647
Because times
have changed.

11:20.681 --> 11:22.082
These girls today...

11:22.616 --> 11:23.984
Oh, they run wild.

11:30.557 --> 11:32.158
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

11:33.059 --> 11:34.260
Hey.

11:34.294 --> 11:35.428
So how was dinner?

11:35.461 --> 11:37.964
Your mother and I
don't want you spending
any more time

11:37.998 --> 11:39.365
with Kim Kelly.
Do you understand?

11:39.399 --> 11:40.901
No, Dad,
she's my friend.

11:40.934 --> 11:42.703
I mean, yes,
she's not like Millie, but...

11:42.736 --> 11:44.505
HAROLD: No, she's not
like Millie all right.

11:44.538 --> 11:48.308
She's as dumb as a crayon.
Even her own mother says so.

11:48.341 --> 11:51.512
Dad, just because
Kim's mother is insane...

11:51.545 --> 11:55.582
No, she's not insane, honey,
she's practically a saint.

11:55.616 --> 11:57.217
Lindsay, do you know
what happens

11:57.250 --> 12:00.621
when you put
a rotten banana
in a fruit bowl?

12:00.654 --> 12:02.989
All the other
bananas go rotten.

12:03.023 --> 12:05.692
And that's what
Kim Kelly is:
a bad banana.

12:05.726 --> 12:09.663
Mrs. Kelly had some
pretty alarming things
to tell us about Kim.

12:09.696 --> 12:10.864
Like what?

12:10.897 --> 12:12.533
HAROLD: That she experiments.

12:12.566 --> 12:13.734
With drugs!

12:13.767 --> 12:15.836
And boys!

12:15.869 --> 12:17.370
Is that true,
honey?

12:21.407 --> 12:22.543
HAROLD: Enough said.

12:22.576 --> 12:24.344
Now, no more Kim Kelly!

12:27.413 --> 12:29.750
You know, maybe she
needs her head shrunk.

12:29.783 --> 12:31.752
Harold...

12:31.785 --> 12:33.654
It's about trust,
and frankly,

12:33.687 --> 12:35.288
I don't think
I trust her anymore.

12:35.321 --> 12:37.724
Lindsay's always been
very honest with us.

12:37.758 --> 12:39.059
Yeah.

12:39.092 --> 12:40.627
Well, she told us
she didn't cheat.

12:40.661 --> 12:41.895
We believed her.

12:42.896 --> 12:45.398
We ended up with egg
on our faces.

12:45.431 --> 12:47.200
Does Lindsay
have a diary?

12:48.635 --> 12:51.271
Yeah. I think
I've seen her
writing in it.

12:53.607 --> 12:55.676
Harold, no!

12:55.709 --> 12:57.744
That is her
private property.

12:57.778 --> 12:59.880
I just wanna know
what's going on.

12:59.913 --> 13:02.415
I had a diary
when I was little.

13:02.448 --> 13:04.751
If my parents had
read it, I would've
been furious.

13:04.785 --> 13:07.921
It's such
a violation.

13:07.954 --> 13:09.222
Spooning
with a stranger

13:09.255 --> 13:11.424
in the back seat of a van,
that's a violation!

13:11.457 --> 13:13.226
She hasn't done that.

13:15.962 --> 13:17.798
There's only one way
to know for sure.

13:20.567 --> 13:22.268
Good night, dear.
Good night.

13:27.007 --> 13:30.577
Oy. I've got
the worst gas.

13:30.611 --> 13:31.845
Please don't.

13:41.788 --> 13:43.223
All right,
I want Crisp.

13:46.660 --> 13:47.761
You heard him,
Crisp, come on.

13:47.794 --> 13:49.029
Join your team.

13:51.732 --> 13:53.066
You wanna play
shortstop?

13:54.334 --> 13:58.171
No. No, I like playing
back‐up right.

13:58.471 --> 14:00.006
You sure?

14:00.040 --> 14:02.075
Yeah, I like
playing back‐up.

14:03.844 --> 14:05.111
I can play shortstop.

14:05.145 --> 14:07.714
Yeah. And, uh, I'm
married to Raquel Welch.

14:07.748 --> 14:09.249
In my dreams.

14:09.282 --> 14:11.251
Phillips, your pick.

14:11.284 --> 14:15.321
All right,
I'm gonna take, uh,
not Haverchuck.

14:16.456 --> 14:18.258
Heh heh. Funny.

14:22.829 --> 14:24.130
Hey!

14:24.164 --> 14:24.998
Hey, Kim.

14:25.031 --> 14:27.333
So my mom, like,
loved your parents.

14:27.367 --> 14:28.502
Guess it went all right.

14:28.535 --> 14:29.703
Yeah, I guess.

14:29.736 --> 14:31.304
What did your
parents say?

14:31.337 --> 14:33.173
Oh, they really
liked your mom.

14:33.206 --> 14:36.209
Cool. You know,
I'm glad it worked out.

14:37.377 --> 14:38.879
And they also said...

14:38.912 --> 14:41.682
Oh, they're such dorks.

14:41.715 --> 14:42.883
Get this.

14:42.916 --> 14:45.251
I'm not allowed
to hang out with you.

14:48.722 --> 14:49.990
It'll blow over.

14:50.023 --> 14:52.025
We've just got
to wait it out
a while, you know?

14:55.195 --> 14:56.597
Oh.

14:56.630 --> 14:58.098
Well, what did
