stick up for her.

31:13.874 --> 31:15.308
I tried.

31:16.242 --> 31:17.878
She's still mad.

31:17.911 --> 31:20.046
I know, but mostly
just her feelings are hurt.

31:20.847 --> 31:22.282
Oh, really?

31:22.315 --> 31:25.385
Hmm. Thought Kim was
too tough to have
her feelings hurt.

31:26.587 --> 31:27.654
Yeah, right.

31:28.221 --> 31:29.122
Kim?

31:29.155 --> 31:31.892
She's like the rawest
nerve there is.

31:31.925 --> 31:34.795
Yeah. She's like
a body without skin.

31:34.828 --> 31:35.962
She's like a bloody...

31:35.996 --> 31:38.331
Okay! I get it.

31:38.364 --> 31:40.200
Can you do it soon?

31:40.233 --> 31:42.503
'Cause she's really
being a pain in my ass.

31:43.203 --> 31:44.771
Yeah, okay.

31:44.805 --> 31:46.640
Great. I owe you my life.

31:47.207 --> 31:48.208
Thanks.

31:50.744 --> 31:52.513
All right!

31:52.546 --> 31:55.749
Haverchuck here
is one of our
captains today.

31:55.782 --> 31:57.317
Shouldn't
the team captain

31:57.350 --> 31:59.319
actually know how
to play baseball?

31:59.352 --> 32:01.855
Don't question me,
people, okay?

32:01.888 --> 32:03.323
Who's the other captain?

32:03.757 --> 32:05.058
Gordon Crisp.

32:05.926 --> 32:07.327
Gordon Crisp it is.

32:07.728 --> 32:09.195
Come on.

32:09.229 --> 32:11.497
BILL: Okay.
Who should I pick first?

32:11.532 --> 32:15.769
I need a power hitter
who can hustle in the field,

32:15.802 --> 32:17.704
with a strong arm.

32:17.738 --> 32:18.805
Gimme Weir.

32:18.839 --> 32:19.873
Come on, Weir.

32:19.906 --> 32:21.642
Yes! Ha ha ha!

32:21.675 --> 32:23.810
Ha ha ha!

32:23.844 --> 32:25.078
Gimme Lewis.

32:28.549 --> 32:29.616
Um...

32:29.650 --> 32:33.153
Now, we need a little speed
around the base pads.

32:34.187 --> 32:36.389
Uh, Schweiber.
Come on, Schweiber.

32:36.422 --> 32:37.524
Yes!

32:37.558 --> 32:39.626
Yeah!
Yeah, yeah!

32:39.660 --> 32:43.630
Oh, man, the geeks have
inherited the Earth.

32:43.664 --> 32:48.869
Today we are going to
continue our discussion
of <i>On the Road.</i>

32:48.902 --> 32:53.206
Ms. Proetzel's comments
last time about
pioneer symbolism

32:53.239 --> 32:55.542
were particularly
interesting.

32:55.576 --> 33:02.048
Ms. Kelly, I am sure
that you have some
original insights.

33:02.082 --> 33:05.552
Tell me what,
in your opinion,

33:05.586 --> 33:08.689
is the theme
of <i>On the Road?</i>

33:11.257 --> 33:14.795
The theme...
Of <i>On the Road</i>

33:14.828 --> 33:16.429
is...

33:20.500 --> 33:22.569
The theme's about...

33:25.706 --> 33:27.774
The theme is...

33:27.808 --> 33:29.776
America

33:29.810 --> 33:31.277
and...

33:33.814 --> 33:35.616
Being...

33:37.417 --> 33:39.019
On the road.

33:39.986 --> 33:43.089
On the Roadis about
being on the road.

33:43.123 --> 33:44.858
(LAUGHTER)
That's good.

33:44.891 --> 33:46.793
That's good.

33:47.828 --> 33:49.129
You... Go on.

33:51.364 --> 33:54.367
I hated the book,
all right?

33:54.400 --> 33:56.136
I have no idea
what it's about,

33:56.169 --> 33:58.839
and the writer was clearly
on drugs when he wrote it.

33:58.872 --> 34:01.875
I mean, it went on
and on and on,

34:01.908 --> 34:04.811
like it was written
in a total hurry.

34:04.845 --> 34:06.179
If I handed in
something like this,

34:06.212 --> 34:08.148
there's no way I'd get
a good grade on it.

34:08.181 --> 34:11.184
I mean, it's boring,
and it's unorganized,

34:11.217 --> 34:13.954
and I only read
30 pages of it anyway.

34:13.987 --> 34:15.856
Well, that was
passionate,

34:15.889 --> 34:18.391
albeit entirely
misinformed.

34:18.424 --> 34:24.264
Who dares follows
Miss Kelly's
lucid analysis, hmm?

34:24.698 --> 34:26.199
Yes.

34:26.232 --> 34:28.034
Well, I think Kim's right.

34:28.068 --> 34:29.369
Kerouac was high
on Benzedrine

34:29.402 --> 34:31.838
during the three weeks he took
to write <i>On the Road.</i>

34:31.872 --> 34:33.574
The structure of the story
isn't strong,

34:33.607 --> 34:36.176
and his experiments with
prose style are tedious.

34:36.209 --> 34:39.946
In fact, Truman Capote
said about <i>On the Road,</i>

34:39.980 --> 34:42.282
"That isn't writing.
It's typing."

34:45.819 --> 34:47.588
Pearls before swine.

34:49.289 --> 34:50.757
What the hell
does that mean?

34:50.791 --> 34:52.092
(LAUGHTER)

34:53.527 --> 34:56.830
Hey, man, sure had
a lot of fun
with your wife last night.

34:56.863 --> 34:58.098
My what?

35:01.334 --> 35:03.236
Ball four. Take your base.

35:04.404 --> 35:06.472
I mean,
a lot of fun!

35:10.310 --> 35:12.546
What's the matter with you?
Are you hurt?

35:12.579 --> 35:14.581
Um... Time!

35:14.615 --> 35:15.749
All right, time out!

35:18.084 --> 35:20.120
What? I told you
I couldn't pitch.

35:20.153 --> 35:21.988
It's not about
your pitching, Sam.

35:22.022 --> 35:23.790
Then what are you
doing out here?

35:25.191 --> 35:27.794
I just always wanted to call
a meeting on the mound.

35:28.629 --> 35:29.896
This is so cool.

35:30.396 --> 35:31.231
Hey.

35:31.264 --> 35:32.766
Meeting
on the mound?

35:33.433 --> 35:34.334
Very cool.

35:34.367 --> 35:38.204
Listen, Bill,
I've got nothing left.

35:38.238 --> 35:41.141
Why don't you just let
one of those jocks pitch?

35:41.174 --> 35:43.076
What are you
talking about?

35:43.109 --> 35:44.878
This is our game.

35:44.911 --> 35:47.113
We can do this.

35:47.147 --> 35:48.481
I don't want them to think
they were right

35:48.515 --> 35:51.484
for putting me
in deep right field
for 11 years.

35:51.852 --> 35:53.286
Come on!

35:54.020 --> 35:55.255
Come on!

35:56.189 --> 35:57.791
He's the butt patter.

35:58.124 --> 35:59.425
Ugh!

36:00.561 --> 36:03.196
(THEME FROM ROCKY PLAYING)

37:33.787 --> 37:35.756
Yeah! (LAUGHING)

37:37.991 --> 37:39.259
Tag up!

37:39.893 --> 37:42.729
We did it!
We did it!

37:43.063 --> 37:44.330
Tag up!

37:45.599 --> 37:48.835
That's the first out,
you morons!

37:52.939 --> 37:54.575
Huh?
Oh.

37:55.141 --> 37:56.510
Well...

37:56.543 --> 37:58.845
Only eight and two‐thirds
more innings to go.

37:58.879 --> 38:00.013
Yeah!

38:00.614 --> 38:01.548
Ha ha!

38:01.582 --> 38:03.750
You see that?
I looked like Willie Mays!

38:06.920 --> 38:08.955
Hey, Kim, Kim.

38:09.756 --> 38:10.757
Kim!

38:11.958 --> 38:12.993
Yeah?

38:13.026 --> 38:15.028
Can I talk to you
for a minute?

38:15.061 --> 38:16.496
What do you want?

38:17.998 --> 38:19.566
What are you doing
right now?

38:22.102 --> 38:23.403
Nothing.

38:24.404 --> 38:25.972
Do you wanna
come over my house?

38:27.073 --> 38:28.408
I thought
we could hang out.

38:29.643 --> 38:31.812
Well, what about
your parents?

38:32.813 --> 38:33.914
What about them?

38:41.054 --> 38:43.023
Daniel,
I'll see you later.

38:43.056 --> 38:44.490
I'm gonna go over
to Lindsay's.

38:44.525 --> 38:46.927
Okay. Later.
God, this is good.

38:46.960 --> 38:48.695
Another day
of hanging out
with him,

38:48.729 --> 38:50.897
and I'd
puke my guts out.

38:50.931 --> 38:52.465
Swear to God.

38:54.535 --> 38:58.204
Jean, is the grocery store
out of normal food?

38:58.238 --> 38:59.272
Is that the problem?

38:59.305 --> 39:00.641
This is normal food.

39:00.674 --> 39:03.076
No. Normal food
is pot roast.

39:03.109 --> 39:04.477
Normal food is meat loaf.

39:04.511 --> 39:07.881
It is dead animal,
and it is not on fire.

39:09.916 --> 39:12.819
No! No! No, no!

39:20.026 --> 39:23.564
Maybe some of us are up
for something a little
different around here.

39:23.597 --> 39:26.066
Don't you wanna
live life, Harold?

39:26.099 --> 39:29.102
Or maybe you've
just turned into
a mean old man.

39:32.906 --> 39:34.174
(SOBBING)

39:34.207 --> 39:36.510
Don't you run away from me!

39:36.543 --> 39:39.245
What's wrong with us,
Harold?

39:39.279 --> 39:41.447
What's happened to us?

39:43.016 --> 39:44.985
We need change,
don't we?

39:45.018 --> 39:47.320
Things need
to change.

39:47.353 --> 39:50.223
I don't want us
to just be robots.

39:50.256 --> 39:51.525
We are not robots,

39:51.558 --> 39:53.527
and things do not
need to change.

39:53.560 --> 39:55.361
I like how things are.

39:55.395 --> 39:57.297
I like eating
the same things.

39:57.330 --> 39:58.565
And you know why?

39:58.599 --> 40:00.567
Because those are
the things I like.

40:00.601 --> 40:03.203
I like chicken,
and I like pot roast.

40:03.236 --> 40:05.706
And that's how I feel
about you, Jean.

40:05.739 --> 40:07.273
Oh, please.

40:07.307 --> 40:10.243
You like me like you
like a pot roast?

40:10.276 --> 40:12.345
I love pot roast!

40:12.378 --> 40:15.281
God, you just
don't get it, do you?

40:15.315 --> 40:17.884
I give up! I quit!

40:17.918 --> 40:19.119
Is that right?

40:19.152 --> 40:21.722
Yes! You don't
appreciate me.

40:21.755 --> 40:23.489
Maybe I'll go back
to school.

40:23.524 --> 40:24.791
What about that?

40:26.693 --> 40:28.995
You think
I don't appreciate you?

40:30.030 --> 40:31.431
Well, I do.

40:35.268 --> 40:37.971
Everything I do,
I do to serve you.

40:39.039 --> 40:40.340
I think of you when I'm...

40:40.373 --> 40:43.877
Stocking fishing poles,
and...

40:43.910 --> 40:49.650
I think of you when I'm
answering questions about
cross‐country ski wax.

40:49.683 --> 40:52.586
My whole life
is about serving you.

40:54.120 --> 40:55.656
And I love you, Jean.

41:02.028 --> 41:03.229
Thank you.

41:06.299 --> 41:07.801
You mean it?

41:17.243 --> 41:19.212
Mom, Dad, we're home.

41:21.815 --> 41:23.249
Ooh.

41:23.283 --> 41:25.051
Is this what's for dinner?

41:26.687 --> 41:27.721
Ugh.

41:32.025 --> 41:33.193
Mom?

41:34.194 --> 41:35.495
Mom?

41:43.904 --> 41:45.506
Mom? Dad?

41:48.441 --> 41:51.712
(JEAN LAUGHING)
(HAROLD GRUNTING)

41:52.178 --> 41:53.947
Ew!

41:54.781 --> 41:56.650
Oh, God.
Let's get outta here.

42:00.386 --> 42:01.487
Neal!

42:01.522 --> 42:03.289
Those are my parents!

42:03.323 --> 42:05.191
Okay, okay.

42:06.426 --> 42:07.994
God, you're gross.

42:08.328 --> 42:09.930
What?

42:09.963 --> 42:11.297
Hey, Linds...

42:12.733 --> 42:13.967
I know what you're
trying to do,

42:14.000 --> 42:16.903
but, you know,
we don't have
to do this.

42:17.137 --> 42:18.171
No.

42:18.204 --> 42:19.973
I want to.

42:20.006 --> 42:22.576
All right, but if they
call the cops on me,

42:22.609 --> 42:23.910
I'm outta here.

42:27.480 --> 42:28.815
NEAL: Hey, Lindsay.

42:29.950 --> 42:32.719
I was catcher
in gym class today.

42:33.453 --> 42:35.055
That's great, Neal.

42:35.088 --> 42:36.089
Where's Mom and Dad?

42:36.590 --> 42:38.592
In their room.

42:38.625 --> 42:40.661
Yeah, they've
been in there
for over an hour.

42:40.694 --> 42:42.062
Are they fighting?

42:43.730 --> 42:44.865
No.

42:47.500 --> 42:49.903
Oh! Hi, sweetie!

42:50.403 --> 42:51.838
Hi, Mom.

42:51.872 --> 42:54.107
Uh, I think we're gonna
order food in tonight,

42:54.140 --> 42:56.943
so maybe you could call
a pizza place

42:56.977 --> 43:00.046
and have them deliver.
HAROLD: Jean!

43:01.214 --> 43:02.616
Hey, Dad...

43:03.216 --> 43:04.350
Kim's here.

43:04.384 --> 43:06.119
She gave me
a ride home
from school.

43:06.620 --> 43:08.054
Hi, Mr. Weir.

43:08.088 --> 43:09.556
Nice to see you, Kim.

43:09.590 --> 43:11.692
Thanks for giving
Lindsay a ride home.

43:11.725 --> 43:14.027
Jean, could I have
a word with you, please?

43:14.060 --> 43:16.830
Yeah. Your father
and I are gonna
be in our room,

43:16.863 --> 43:19.399
so let us know when
the food gets here.

43:19.432 --> 43:21.768
You kids play nice
now, you hear?

43:26.239 --> 43:28.341
Oh, my God.

43:29.242 --> 43:31.277
Lindsay...

43:31.311 --> 43:33.614
Your parents are swingers.
